A monograph filled with medical accounts of aetheric imbalance. In remarkably good condition.
A carefully hidden scrap of parchment inscribed with a riddle: “Four lamps loom over streets of glass, but only one true light shines on Her Majesty.”
A cunningly concealed scrap of parchment inscribed with a riddle: “Over the river, in sight of the spiral, behind the pointy hat hide the shrubs you seek.”

An elaborate diagram of the Meso Terminal and the golden statue at its head, depicted from several angles.
Faintly fragrant of the versatile, ever-popular fruit.

The monster within struggles in vain against its fate.

A bundle of aether-rich reeds plucked straight from the paddy.
